    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-divider guten-element guten-divider guten-jBXkeU\"><div class=\"guten-divider-wrapper\"><div class=\"guten-divider-default guten-divider-line guten-divider-regular\"></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"section-wrapper\" data-id=\"wiyYMs\"><section class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-section guten-element guten-section guten-wiyYMs layout-boxed align-stretch\"><div class=\"guten-container guten-column-gap-default\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-column guten-element guten-column guten-MU3K8L\"><div class=\"guten-column-wrapper\" data-id=\"MU3K8L\">\n<p>Major Ofek Bachar, a 24-year-old resident of Ness Ziona, served as a company commander in the Golani Brigade&#8217;s elite reconnaissance unit. On October 16, 2024, during a mission in southern Lebanon, he and four of his comrades fell in battle against Hezbollah militants. This tragic event occurred amidst the Iron Swords War, which began on October 7, 2023, following a brutal attack by Hamas terrorists and Palestinians, leading to significant Israeli casualties and ongoing conflict.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Family Life</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Born to Yehuda and Ronit Bachar, Ofek was a cherished son and brother to Shagai and Ofir. He grew up in Ness Ziona and was an alumnus of Golda School. His family and friends remember him as a courageous individual who was deeply loved and surrounded by many who stood by him throughout his journey.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Military Service and Heroic Sacrifice</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Ofek&#8217;s military career was marked by dedication and bravery. He began his service in the esteemed Egoz Unit, where he honed his skills and leadership qualities. In mid-2024, he transitioned to the Golani Brigade&#8217;s reconnaissance unit, taking command of a company. His leadership was characterized by leading from the front, always at the forefront of his troops.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On October 7, 2024, while on leave, Ofek and his friends responded to the attacks by descending to Kfar Aza, where they engaged in combat and assisted in evacuating the wounded. During this operation, he sustained a gunshot wound to the shoulder. Demonstrating remarkable resilience, he returned to his unit shortly after, continuing to lead his soldiers despite his injury.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Tragically, on October 16, 2024, during a mission to locate terrorist infrastructure in a building in southern Lebanon, Ofek and his team encountered hidden Hezbollah militants. A fierce firefight ensued, resulting in the elimination of the terrorists but at the cost of Ofek&#8217;s life and those of four fellow soldiers.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Personal Achievements</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Ofek&#8217;s commitment to his country and his comrades was unwavering. Even after being wounded, he chose to return to the battlefield, exemplifying his dedication and courage. His actions during the Iron Swords War reflect a profound sense of duty and heroism.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Legacy</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The city of Ness Ziona mourned the loss of Ofek, honoring him as a brave and dedicated soldier. His funeral was held at the military cemetery in Ness Ziona, with the community expressing deep condolences to his family.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ofek Bachar&#8217;s life and service are a testament to the valor and sacrifice of those who defend their nation. His memory serves as an enduring inspiration, embodying the spirit of dedication and bravery in the face of adversity.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-column guten-element guten-column guten-AswJbl soldier-details-sidebar\"><div class=\"guten-column-wrapper\" data-id=\"AswJbl\">\n<div class=\"section-wrapper\" data-id=\"Zvaq3t\"><section class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-section guten-element guten-section guten-Zvaq3t layout-fullwidth align-stretch\"><div class=\"guten-container guten-column-gap-default\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-column guten-element guten-column guten-EAQ3rE\"><div class=\"guten-column-wrapper\" data-id=\"EAQ3rE\">\n<div class=\"section-wrapper\" data-id=\"yYHti5\"><section class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-section guten-element guten-section guten-yYHti5 layout-boxed align-stretch\"><div class=\"guten-container guten-column-gap-default\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-column guten-element guten-column guten-SEpzy9\"><div class=\"guten-column-wrapper\" data-id=\"SEpzy9\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-image guten-element guten-image guten-5FaiZf\"><div class=\"guten-image-wrapper\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"gutenverse-image-box-filled\" src=\"https://iron-swords.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/candle.png\" height=\"3558\" width=\"1192\"/></div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-column guten-element guten-column guten-swlawj\"><div class=\"guten-column-wrapper\" data-id=\"swlawj\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-vPCsyp\">First Name</h4>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-HAat4n\">Ofek</h5>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-Jifb7c\">Last Name</h4>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-kN0HGq\">Bacher</h2>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-C01tAO\">Age</h4>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-sMCOfV\">24</h5>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-6jjF2C\">Fell On</h4>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-ZCTvou\">Army Unit</h4>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-rzyyzT\">golani</h2>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-tgoGW2\">Army Rank</h4>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-VbyEYK\">Major</h2>\n</div></div>\n</div></section></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-gutenverse-heading guten-element guten-4OvJpt\">\u05d9\u05d4\u05d9 \u05d6\u05db\u05e8\u05d5 \u05d1\u05e8\u05d5\u05da</h2>\n</div></div>\n</div></section></div>\n\n\n</div></div>\n</div></section></div>\n",
